{
  "description": "Fauci email replied-to network (Fauci removed), 32 nodes, 63 directed edges. Edge u->v (weight w) means u replied to v's email w times. Weights are genuinely asymmetric: 27 one-way edges, 36 edges with a reciprocal.",
  "source": {
    "paper": "arXiv:2108.01239",
    "authors": [
      "Austin R. Benson",
      "Nate Veldt",
      "David F. Gleich"
    ],
    "repo": "https://github.com/nveldt/fauci-email",
    "construction": "For each email thread, sort by timestamp; email i+1 is a reply to email i. Edge from replier to previous sender, weight = count of such replies."
  },
  "layout": {
    "algorithm": "Fruchterman-Reingold (600 iterations, gravity=0.05)",
    "width": 800,
    "height": 600
  },
